A number of clubs in the Nigeria Premier Football League are circling around free agent forward, Chinemerem Igboeli, according to reports. Igboeli is seeking a fresh start after leaving Russian club, FDC Vista. DAILY POST learnt that Nasarawa United, Dakkada, Wikki Tourists and Bayelsa United are jostling for the playerâ€™s signature. Igboeli had stint with Heartland Football Club of Owerri and defunct FC Ifeanyi Ubah before moving to Russia. The striker is in talks with the four clubs and is expected to make a decision on his future soon. The transfer window in the NPFL is currently open for clubs to bring in new players.